{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":884,"text":"I'm going to be talking\nabout statistics today."},{"time":3671,"text":"If that makes you immediately feel\na little bit wary, that's OK,"},{"time":6833,"text":"that doesn't make you some\nkind of crazy conspiracy theorist,"},{"time":9716,"text":"it makes you skeptical."},{"time":11036,"text":"And when it comes to numbers,\nespecially now, you should be skeptical."},{"time":14946,"text":"But you should also be able to tell\nwhich numbers are reliable"},{"time":17981,"text":"and which ones aren't."},{"time":19165,"text":"So today I want to try to give you\nsome tools to be able to do that."},{"time":22395,"text":"But before I do,"},{"time":23588,"text":"I just want to clarify which numbers\nI'm talking about here."},{"time":26451,"text":"I'm not talking about claims like,"},{"time":28110,"text":"\"9 out of 10 women recommend\nthis anti-aging cream.\""},{"time":30583,"text":"I think a lot of us always\nroll our eyes at numbers like that."},{"time":33579,"text":"What's different now is people\nare questioning statistics like,"},{"time":36587,"text":"\"The US unemployment\nrate is five percent.\""},{"time":38625,"text":"What makes this claim different is\nit doesn't come from a private company,"},{"time":42165,"text":"it comes from the government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43577,"text":"About 4 out of 10 Americans\ndistrust the economic data"},{"time":46937,"text":"that gets reported by government."},{"time":48534,"text":"Among supporters of President Trump\nit's even higher;"},{"time":51049,"text":"it's about 7 out of 10."},{"time":52706,"text":"I don't need to tell anyone here"},{"time":54534,"text":"that there are a lot of dividing lines\nin our society right now,"},{"time":57569,"text":"and a lot of them start to make sense,"},{"time":59418,"text":"once you understand people's relationships\nwith these government numbers."},{"time":63129,"text":"On the one hand, there are those who say\nthese statistics are crucial,"},{"time":66489,"text":"that we need them to make sense\nof society as a whole"},{"time":69143,"text":"in order to move beyond\nemotional anecdotes"},{"time":71331,"text":"and measure progress\nin an [objective] way."},{"time":73765,"text":"And then there are the others,"},{"time":75256,"text":"who say that these statistics are elitist,"},{"time":77436,"text":"maybe even rigged;"},{"time":78668,"text":"they don't make sense\nand they don't really reflect"},{"time":81086,"text":"what's happening\nin people's everyday lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83406,"text":"It kind of feels like that second group\nis winning the argument right now."},{"time":86917,"text":"We're living in a world\nof alternative facts,"},{"time":89049,"text":"where people don't find statistics\nthis kind of common ground,"},{"time":92008,"text":"this starting point for debate."},{"time":93668,"text":"This is a problem."},{"time":94978,"text":"There are actually\nmoves in the US right now"},{"time":97069,"text":"to get rid of some government\nstatistics altogether."},{"time":99954,"text":"Right now there's a bill in congress\nabout measuring racial inequality."},{"time":103365,"text":"The draft law says that government\nmoney should not be used"},{"time":106190,"text":"to collect data on racial segregation."},{"time":108116,"text":"This is a total disaster."},{"time":110025,"text":"If we don't have this data,"},{"time":111797,"text":"how can we observe discrimination,"},{"time":113599,"text":"let alone fix it?"},{"time":114901,"text":"In other words:"},{"time":116113,"text":"How can a government create fair policies"},{"time":118196,"text":"if they can't measure\ncurrent levels of unfairness?"},{"time":120991,"text":"This isn't just about discrimination,"},{"time":122809,"text":"it's everything -- think about it."},{"time":124503,"text":"How can we legislate on health care"},{"time":126217,"text":"if we don't have good data\non health or poverty?"},{"time":128512,"text":"How can we have public debate\nabout immigration"},{"time":130734,"text":"if we can't at least agree"},{"time":132008,"text":"on how many people are entering\nand leaving the country?"},{"time":134675,"text":"Statistics come from the state;\nthat's where they got their name."},{"time":137757,"text":"The point was to better\nmeasure the population"},{"time":139938,"text":"in order to better serve it."},{"time":141319,"text":"So we need these government numbers,"},{"time":143068,"text":"but we also have to move\nbeyond either blindly accepting"},{"time":145739,"text":"or blindly rejecting them."},{"time":147031,"text":"We need to learn the skills\nto be able to spot bad statistics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150052,"text":"I started to learn some of these"},{"time":151604,"text":"when I was working\nin a statistical department"},{"time":153794,"text":"that's part of the United Nations."},{"time":155461,"text":"Our job was to find out how many Iraqis\nhad been forced from their homes"},{"time":158891,"text":"as a result of the war,"},{"time":160073,"text":"and what they needed."},{"time":161255,"text":"It was really important work,\nbut it was also incredibly difficult."},{"time":164457,"text":"Every single day, we were making decisions"},{"time":166499,"text":"that affected the accuracy\nof our numbers --"},{"time":168680,"text":"decisions like which parts\nof the country we should go to,"},{"time":171448,"text":"who we should speak to,"},{"time":172628,"text":"which questions we should ask."},{"time":174220,"text":"And I started to feel\nreally disillusioned with our work,"},{"time":176924,"text":"because we thought we were doing\na really good job,"},{"time":179466,"text":"but the one group of people\nwho could really tell us were the Iraqis,"},{"time":182768,"text":"and they rarely got the chance to find\nour analysis, let alone question it."},{"time":186332,"text":"So I started to feel really determined"},{"time":188187,"text":"that the one way to make\nnumbers more accurate"},{"time":190522,"text":"is to have as many people as possible\nbe able to question them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193599,"text":"So I became a data journalist."},{"time":195057,"text":"My job is finding these data sets\nand sharing them with the public."},{"time":198985,"text":"Anyone can do this,\nyou don't have to be a geek or a nerd."},{"time":202182,"text":"You can ignore those words;\nthey're used by people"},{"time":204561,"text":"trying to say they're smart\nwhile pretending they're humble."},{"time":207407,"text":"Absolutely anyone can do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209020,"text":"I want to give you guys three questions"},{"time":211111,"text":"that will help you be able to spot\nsome bad statistics."},{"time":214140,"text":"So, question number one\nis: Can you see uncertainty?"},{"time":217671,"text":"One of things that's really changed\npeople's relationship with numbers,"},{"time":221059,"text":"and even their trust in the media,"},{"time":222724,"text":"has been the use of political polls."},{"time":225006,"text":"I personally have a lot of issues\nwith political polls"},{"time":227568,"text":"because I think the role of journalists\nis actually to report the facts"},{"time":230968,"text":"and not attempt to predict them,"},{"time":232545,"text":"especially when those predictions\ncan actually damage democracy"},{"time":235565,"text":"by signaling to people:\ndon't bother to vote for that guy,"},{"time":238321,"text":"he doesn't have a chance."},{"time":239550,"text":"Let's set that aside for now and talk\nabout the accuracy of this endeavor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243228,"text":"Based on national elections\nin the UK, Italy, Israel"},{"time":247860,"text":"and of course, the most recent\nUS presidential election,"},{"time":250648,"text":"using polls to predict electoral outcomes"},{"time":252809,"text":"is about as accurate as using the moon\nto predict hospital admissions."},{"time":256645,"text":"No, seriously, I used actual data\nfrom an academic study to draw this."},{"time":260869,"text":"There are a lot of reasons why\npolling has become so inaccurate."},{"time":264620,"text":"Our societies have become really diverse,"},{"time":266614,"text":"which makes it difficult for pollsters\nto get a really nice representative sample"},{"time":270459,"text":"of the population for their polls."},{"time":272110,"text":"People are really reluctant to answer\ntheir phones to pollsters,"},{"time":275140,"text":"and also, shockingly enough,\npeople might lie."},{"time":277440,"text":"But you wouldn't necessarily\nknow that to look at the media."},{"time":280275,"text":"For one thing, the probability\nof a Hillary Clinton win"},{"time":283060,"text":"was communicated with decimal places."},{"time":285875,"text":"We don't use decimal places\nto describe the temperature."},{"time":288520,"text":"How on earth can predicting the behavior\nof 230 million voters in this country"},{"time":292772,"text":"be that precise?"},{"time":294625,"text":"And then there were those sleek charts."},{"time":296651,"text":"See, a lot of data visualizations\nwill overstate certainty, and it works --"},{"time":300648,"text":"these charts can numb\nour brains to criticism."},{"time":303292,"text":"When you hear a statistic,\nyou might feel skeptical."},{"time":305874,"text":"As soon as it's buried in a chart,"},{"time":307533,"text":"it feels like some kind\nof objective science,"},{"time":309686,"text":"and it's not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310959,"text":"So I was trying to find ways\nto better communicate this to people,"},{"time":314086,"text":"to show people the uncertainty\nin our numbers."},{"time":316614,"text":"What I did was I started taking\nreal data sets,"},{"time":318884,"text":"and turning them into\nhand-drawn visualizations,"},{"time":321560,"text":"so that people can see\nhow imprecise the data is;"},{"time":324256,"text":"so people can see that a human did this,"},{"time":326276,"text":"a human found the data and visualized it."},{"time":328272,"text":"For example, instead\nof finding out the probability"},{"time":330968,"text":"of getting the flu in any given month,"},{"time":333118,"text":"you can see the rough\ndistribution of flu season."},{"time":335934,"text":"This is --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":337125,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":338167,"text":"a bad shot to show in February."},{"time":339677,"text":"But it's also more responsible\ndata visualization,"},{"time":342156,"text":"because if you were to show\nthe exact probabilities,"},{"time":344635,"text":"maybe that would encourage\npeople to get their flu jabs"},{"time":347251,"text":"at the wrong time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349163,"text":"The point of these shaky lines"},{"time":350880,"text":"is so that people remember\nthese imprecisions,"},{"time":353815,"text":"but also so they don't necessarily\nwalk away with a specific number,"},{"time":357066,"text":"but they can remember important facts."},{"time":358956,"text":"Facts like injustice and inequality\nleave a huge mark on our lives."},{"time":363004,"text":"Facts like Black Americans and Native\nAmericans have shorter life expectancies"},{"time":367217,"text":"than those of other races,"},{"time":368641,"text":"and that isn't changing anytime soon."},{"time":370803,"text":"Facts like prisoners in the US\ncan be kept in solitary confinement cells"},{"time":374728,"text":"that are smaller than the size\nof an average parking space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378535,"text":"The point of these visualizations\nis also to remind people"},{"time":381894,"text":"of some really important\nstatistical concepts,"},{"time":384268,"text":"concepts like averages."},{"time":385928,"text":"So let's say you hear a claim like,"},{"time":387620,"text":"\"The average swimming pool in the US\ncontains 6.23 fecal accidents.\""},{"time":392078,"text":"That doesn't mean every single\nswimming pool in the country"},{"time":394899,"text":"contains exactly 6.23 turds."},{"time":397117,"text":"So in order to show that,"},{"time":398558,"text":"I went back to the original data,\nwhich comes from the CDC,"},{"time":401423,"text":"who surveyed 47 swimming facilities."},{"time":403512,"text":"And I just spent one evening\nredistributing poop."},{"time":405927,"text":"So you can kind of see\nhow misleading averages can be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408633,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":409939,"text":"OK, so the second question\nthat you guys should be asking yourselves"},{"time":413864,"text":"to spot bad numbers is:"},{"time":415389,"text":"Can I see myself in the data?"},{"time":417380,"text":"This question is also\nabout averages in a way,"},{"time":420317,"text":"because part of the reason\nwhy people are so frustrated"},{"time":422946,"text":"with these national statistics,"},{"time":424465,"text":"is they don't really tell the story\nof who's winning and who's losing"},{"time":427762,"text":"from national policy."},{"time":428942,"text":"It's easy to understand why people\nare frustrated with global averages"},{"time":432284,"text":"when they don't match up\nwith their personal experiences."},{"time":434987,"text":"I wanted to show people the way\ndata relates to their everyday lives."},{"time":438274,"text":"I started this advice column\ncalled \"Dear Mona,\""},{"time":440544,"text":"where people would write to me\nwith questions and concerns"},{"time":443294,"text":"and I'd try to answer them with data."},{"time":445102,"text":"People asked me anything."},{"time":446326,"text":"questions like, \"Is it normal to sleep\nin a separate bed to my wife?\""},{"time":449611,"text":"\"Do people regret their tattoos?\""},{"time":451226,"text":"\"What does it mean to die\nof natural causes?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":453414,"text":"All of these questions are great,\nbecause they make you think"},{"time":456404,"text":"about ways to find\nand communicate these numbers."},{"time":458764,"text":"If someone asks you,\n\"How much pee is a lot of pee?\""},{"time":461291,"text":"which is a question that I got asked,"},{"time":463773,"text":"you really want to make sure\nthat the visualization makes sense"},{"time":466777,"text":"to as many people as possible."},{"time":468548,"text":"These numbers aren't unavailable."},{"time":470147,"text":"Sometimes they're just buried\nin the appendix of an academic study."},{"time":473678,"text":"And they're certainly not inscrutable;"},{"time":475541,"text":"if you really wanted to test\nthese numbers on urination volume,"},{"time":478540,"text":"you could grab a bottle\nand try it for yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480821,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":481853,"text":"The point of this isn't necessarily"},{"time":483571,"text":"that every single data set\nhas to relate specifically to you."},{"time":486472,"text":"I'm interested in how many women\nwere issued fines in France"},{"time":489376,"text":"for wearing the face veil, or the niqab,"},{"time":491359,"text":"even if I don't live in France\nor wear the face veil."},{"time":494001,"text":"The point of asking where you fit in\nis to get as much context as possible."},{"time":497860,"text":"So it's about zooming out\nfrom one data point,"},{"time":500075,"text":"like the unemployment rate\nis five percent,"},{"time":502203,"text":"and seeing how it changes over time,"},{"time":503984,"text":"or seeing how it changes\nby educational status --"},{"time":506658,"text":"this is why your parents always\nwanted you to go to college --"},{"time":509786,"text":"or seeing how it varies by gender."},{"time":511842,"text":"Nowadays, male unemployment rate is higher"},{"time":513993,"text":"than the female unemployment rate."},{"time":515717,"text":"Up until the early '80s,\nit was the other way around."},{"time":518436,"text":"This is a story of one\nof the biggest changes"},{"time":520577,"text":"that's happened in American society,"},{"time":522321,"text":"and it's all there in that chart,\nonce you look beyond the averages."},{"time":525621,"text":"The axes are everything;"},{"time":526810,"text":"once you change the scale,\nyou can change the story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529503,"text":"OK, so the third and final question\nthat I want you guys to think about"},{"time":532907,"text":"when you're looking at statistics is:"},{"time":534750,"text":"How was the data collected?"},{"time":537667,"text":"So far, I've only talked about the way\ndata is communicated,"},{"time":540630,"text":"but the way it's collected\nmatters just as much."},{"time":542930,"text":"I know this is tough,"},{"time":544121,"text":"because methodologies can be opaque\nand actually kind of boring,"},{"time":547226,"text":"but there are some simple steps\nyou can take to check this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550123,"text":"I'll use one last example here."},{"time":552309,"text":"One poll found that 41 percent of Muslims\nin this country support jihad,"},{"time":556220,"text":"which is obviously pretty scary,"},{"time":557769,"text":"and it was reported everywhere in 2015."},{"time":560435,"text":"When I want to check a number like that,"},{"time":563074,"text":"I'll start off by finding\nthe original questionnaire."},{"time":565599,"text":"It turns out that journalists\nwho reported on that statistic"},{"time":568549,"text":"ignored a question\nlower down on the survey"},{"time":570804,"text":"that asked respondents\nhow they defined \"jihad.\""},{"time":573174,"text":"And most of them defined it as,"},{"time":575179,"text":"\"Muslims' personal, peaceful struggle\nto be more religious.\""},{"time":579145,"text":"Only 16 percent defined it as,\n\"violent holy war against unbelievers.\""},{"time":583363,"text":"This is the really important point:"},{"time":585817,"text":"based on those numbers,\nit's totally possible"},{"time":587996,"text":"that no one in the survey\nwho defined it as violent holy war"},{"time":591125,"text":"also said they support it."},{"time":592481,"text":"Those two groups might not overlap at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595122,"text":"It's also worth asking\nhow the survey was carried out."},{"time":597783,"text":"This was something called an opt-in poll,"},{"time":599805,"text":"which means anyone could have found it\non the internet and completed it."},{"time":603231,"text":"There's no way of knowing\nif those people even identified as Muslim."},{"time":606594,"text":"And finally, there were 600\nrespondents in that poll."},{"time":609230,"text":"There are roughly three million\nMuslims in this country,"},{"time":611908,"text":"according to Pew Research Center."},{"time":613539,"text":"That means the poll spoke to roughly\none in every 5,000 Muslims"},{"time":616556,"text":"in this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617748,"text":"This is one of the reasons"},{"time":619038,"text":"why government statistics\nare often better than private statistics."},{"time":622669,"text":"A poll might speak to a couple\nhundred people, maybe a thousand,"},{"time":625728,"text":"or if you're L'Oreal, trying to sell\nskin care products in 2005,"},{"time":628810,"text":"then you spoke to 48 women\nto claim that they work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631251,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":632301,"text":"Private companies don't have a huge\ninterest in getting the numbers right,"},{"time":635881,"text":"they just need the right numbers."},{"time":637660,"text":"Government statisticians aren't like that."},{"time":639704,"text":"In theory, at least,\nthey're totally impartial,"},{"time":642175,"text":"not least because most of them do\ntheir jobs regardless of who's in power."},{"time":645700,"text":"They're civil servants."},{"time":646886,"text":"And to do their jobs properly,"},{"time":648874,"text":"they don't just speak\nto a couple hundred people."},{"time":651261,"text":"Those unemployment numbers\nI keep on referencing"},{"time":653603,"text":"come from the Bureau of Labor Statistics,"},{"time":655631,"text":"and to make their estimates,"},{"time":656990,"text":"they speak to over 140,000\nbusinesses in this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660503,"text":"I get it, it's frustrating."},{"time":662252,"text":"If you want to test a statistic\nthat comes from a private company,"},{"time":665391,"text":"you can buy the face cream for you\nand a bunch of friends, test it out,"},{"time":668776,"text":"if it doesn't work,\nyou can say the numbers were wrong."},{"time":671391,"text":"But how do you question\ngovernment statistics?"},{"time":673561,"text":"You just keep checking everything."},{"time":675215,"text":"Find out how they collected the numbers."},{"time":677152,"text":"Find out if you're seeing everything\non the chart you need to see."},{"time":680301,"text":"But don't give up on the numbers\naltogether, because if you do,"},{"time":683290,"text":"we'll be making public policy\ndecisions in the dark,"},{"time":685753,"text":"using nothing but private\ninterests to guide us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688039,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689229,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}